17/06/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia-Montenegro will apply this week to join NATO's Partnership for Peace programme, according to Defence Minister Boris Tadic. In a speech Monday (16 June) marking Serbia-Montenegro Army Day, Tadic said joining the programme is a security priority and a precondition for entering the EU.
In other news, former Yugoslav President Zoran Lilic is expected to appear before the UN war crimes tribunal Tuesday to testify in the trial of Slobodan Milosevic. He is expected to provide evidence of Milosevic's role in the conflicts in Bosnia and Herzegovina and Croatia. (B92, BBC, FoNet, Tanjug, AFP - 16/06/03)
